4. Top games leaderboard

Data: Scrape the first 50 entries of the games leaderboard available here: https://gamesight.io/games. You can use the rvest package in R or another method/language if you prefer. (Hint: use Chrome to save the pages you plan to read with File Save Page As, choosing the Webpage, Complete format. Then read the downloaded .html files with rvest. We will discuss the reason for this extra step in class.)

  1. Draw a parallel coordinates plot of the quantitative variables (not including Rank).
library(tidyverse)
library(GGally)

games <- read_csv("games.csv", col_types = "icnnnnn")
ggparcoord(games, columns = 3:7)

rownames(games) <- games$Name
games |> select(2:6) |> 
parcoords::parcoords(rownames = FALSE,
                     brushMode = "1D-axes",
                     reorderable = TRUE)

  1. What patterns do you observe?

  2. Choose one of the patterns and provide an explanation (hypothesis) for the observed trend based on some research and/or personal knowledge of the topic.
